@page "/"

<PageTitle>Home</PageTitle>

<h1>PurpleHatProject</h1>

<p>A music player web application built with Blazor Server, featuring audio playback, user accounts, favourite tracks, and session persistence.</p>

<div class="alert alert-info">
    <strong>Get started:</strong> Head to the <a href="music"><strong>Music Player</strong></a> to browse tracks, control playback, and manage your favourites.
</div>

<hr />

<h4>Pages</h4>

<ul>
    <li><strong><a href="music">Music Player</a></strong> — The main application. Browse and play tracks, favourite them, control volume, and skip between songs. Log in to persist your favourites and playback session.</li>
</ul>

<p class="text-muted" style="font-size: 0.85rem;">The pages below are development/debugging tools and are not part of the core application:</p>

<ul class="text-muted" style="font-size: 0.85rem;">
    <li><a href="counter">Counter</a> — Verifies Blazor Server real-time interactivity is working.</li>
    <li><a href="db-health">SQLite Health</a> — Tests SQLite connectivity with a read/write round-trip.</li>
    <li><a href="dynamodb-health">DynamoDB Health</a> — Tests DynamoDB connectivity with a read/write round-trip.</li>
</ul>

<hr />

